                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4614.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate, Ciudad Juárez</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1912-08-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1912-07-21T00:00:00-06:57">undated</date>] (<hi rend="italic"
                            >Received August 12, 1912—11.26 p.m.</hi>)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>According to General Orozco, President Madero is to resign in pursuance of a
                    basis for cessation of hostilities which he claims has been agreed upon, to be
                    concluded with General Huerta soon. Casas Grandes district now in control of
                    Federals; conditions better.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
